PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781470070
OL,3,CIs the PM about to attend his last
OL,4,Csummit of world leaders?
OL,6,FWhat happens if they can't agree a
OL,7,Ftransfer of power, if Starmer does
OL,8,Fwhat he says and insists Burnham puts
OL,9,Fup in a formal contest or shuts up?
OL,11,F"That status quo could not last," says
OL,12,Fa minister. "The prime minister's
OL,13,Fauthority is too weakened. There would
OL,14,Fbe a contest, maybe triggered by
OL,15,Fanother candidate."
OL,17,FThe prime minister is said to be
OL,18,Fplotting a survival strategy, as if it
OL,19,Fwere a game of chess. But none of his
OL,20,Fcolleagues - or at least those to whom
OL,21,FI have spoken - think he can win.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@aO]tD@MOUwD@SO]
